quran[13]{c,v,t,f}:
  27,64,"Or who<i>(else then) </i>is the one who originates creation and then restores it, and Who provides for you<sup>pl </sup>from the sky and the land? Is there any other god with Allah? Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Produce your<sup>pl </sup>proof, if you are truthful.”"
  27,65,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “No one in the heavens or the earth knows what is hidden except Allah.” For they are unaware of when they will be resurrected;"
  27,66,"rather, their knowledge has been reached{1}in the Hereafter; rather, they are in doubt about it; rather, they are completely blind to it.",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Ibn Kathir, Abu Amr, Abu Ja’far, and Ya’qub read it as: “…rather, their knowledge has been grasped in the Hereafter;”]
  27,67,"And those who denied said, “Can it be that{1}when we have become dust, and our forefathers—can it be thatwe will really be brought out?",footnotes:1:[Qira’at: Ibn Amer and Al-Kesa’i read it as: “Can it be that when we have become dust, and our forefathers, we will really be brought out?” Nafie’ and Abu Ja’far read it as: “When we have become dust, and our forefathers—can it be that we will really …”]
  27,68,"Most surely, we were promised this before, we and our forefathers; this is nothing but the legends of the ancients.”"
  27,69,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Journey through the earth and look what the outcome was for the criminals.”"
  27,70,"But do<sup>sg </sup>not grieve over them and do not be troubled by what they scheme."
  27,71,"And they say, “When is this promise, if you are truthful?”"
  27,72,"Say<sup>sg </sup>, “Perhaps some of what you are asking to be hastened has drawn near.”"
  27,73,"And indeed, your<sup>sg </sup>Lord is surely the Possessor of grace towards mankind, but most of them are not thankful."
  27,74,"And indeed, your<sup>sg </sup>Lord knows whatever their chests harbor and whatever they make public."
  27,75,"And never is there anything hidden in the heaven or the earth but it is in an evident record{1}.",footnotes:1:[Literally ‘scripture’.]
  27,76,"This Recital{1}indeed narrates to the Children of Israel most of what they differ over,",footnotes:1:[The Arabic word used is <i>Quran</i> which means ‘recital’ or ‘recitation’.]
